    • Method Detail

      • nextRandomInt

        public static int nextRandomInt​(int least,
                                int bound)
        Deprecated.
        Java 8+ users should use ThreadLocalRandom.nextInt(int, int) or SplittableRandom.nextInt(int, int).
        Returns a pseudorandom, uniformly distributed value between the given least value (inclusive) and bound (exclusive) using a default Random instance.

        Note: In most cases you should no longer use Random. ThreadLocalRandom is much quicker and produces higher quality random numbers. SplittableRandom is available for use in ForkJoinPools and parallel streams. Only use Random if you plan to share it across threads (it is thread-safe at the cost of extremely poor performance during high contention).

        Parameters:
        least - the least value
        bound - the upper bound (exclusive)
        Returns:
        a pseudorandom, uniformly distributed value between the given least value (inclusive) and bound (exclusive)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if least < 0 or bound < 0 or least >= bound

      • nextRandomInt

        public static int nextRandomInt​(Random random,
                                int least,
                                int bound)
        Deprecated.
        Java 8+ users should use ThreadLocalRandom.nextInt(int, int) or SplittableRandom.nextInt(int, int).
        Returns a pseudorandom, uniformly distributed value between the given least value (inclusive) and bound (exclusive) using the specified Random instance.

        Note: In most cases you should no longer use Random. ThreadLocalRandom is much quicker and produces higher quality random numbers. SplittableRandom is available for use in ForkJoinPools and parallel streams. Only use Random if you plan to share it across threads (it is thread-safe at the cost of extremely poor performance during high contention).

        Parameters:
        random - the Random instance to use to generate random integers
        least - the least value
        bound - the upper bound (exclusive)
        Returns:
        a pseudorandom, uniformly distributed value between the given least value (inclusive) and bound (exclusive)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if least < 0 or bound < 0 or least >= bound

      • tryParse

        public static Integer tryParse​(String str,
                               Integer defaultValue)
        Parses the specified string as a signed decimal integer value. The ASCII character '-' ('\u002D') is recognized as the minus sign.

        See Guava's Ints.tryParse(String) for more details.

        Parameters:
        str - the string representation of an integer value
        defaultValue - the possibly null value to return if the parsing fails
        Returns:
        the integer value represented by str, or defaultValue if str has a length of zero or cannot be parsed as an integer value
